commitResults.messageBody:
We allow for additional specifiers to further filter through the
contacts found. We also support empty search fields. Predicate uses AND-search with contacts being required to meet all fields. However, for
the name keywords match itself, it is an OR-search.

commitResults.messageBody:
SortedList is used to wrap around the FilteredList as the FilteredList
itself is immutable. The getFilteredPersonList() has been changed to
return the sortedList instead. This makes it such that both filters and
comparators are reflected in the list being shown.

AddressBook was chosen as it is largely a separate implementation from
ReadOnlyAddressBook unlike Model. As such, changing the underlying
functionality does not significantly affect the rest of the program,
especially other stubs that have been implemented.

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement search by tags in Model and implementing classes
commitResults.messageBody:
As the commands only interact with the Model class, Model must contain
the method getPersonsWithTag(Tag).

commitResults.messageTitle: Update handling of non-existent Tag keys
commitResults.messageBody:
When a Tag does not exist in the TagManager, an empty Set will be
returned instead of null. To complement this, when removing Person
objects from a Tag in TagManagerImpl, if the Set becomes empty, the key
is deleted.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add integration tests between AddressBook and TagManager
Change Tag strings to be always lower case
commitResults.messageBody:
This was done to support future features that require lookup by tag. We
would want someone who tags two different contacts as CS2103 and cs2103
to show up in the same search. As such, we have decided to default
casing to lowercase.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Javadocs to TagTree and TagTreeImpl

commitResults.messageBody:
The class integrates the functionality of Person and Tag together by
implementing operations that affect both. AddressBook is used as the
proxy manager for Person and Tag-Person map. TagTree is used to keep
track of only Tag to Tag relationships. This class then supports
operations that makes changes to both.
